Merge pull request #12 from jbenet/master

HTTP and IPFS Support

address CR comments

- fix return bug
- handle no range in stream options

ipfs path resolution

this commit introduces ipfs path resolution. it tries three steps:

1. it first checks a local http gateway at localhost:8080
   (todo make this configurable), deferring to onhttplink
2. if that fails, it attempt to use the mounted filesystem.
3. if that fails, it uses the global gateway at gateway.ipfs.io.

You can try it with:

  npm install -g go-ipfs
  ipfs daemon &
  sleep 10 # wait for bootstrap (this will be better)
  atom-shell app.js /ipfs/QmTKZgRNwDNZwHtJSjCp6r5FYefzpULfy37JvMt9DwvXse/video.mp4

add http link resolution

This commit introduces arbitrary http link resolution. It uses
http-client-stream to create readable http streams, with range
queries. This effectively proxies traffic.

Important note: it must first do a HEAD request to the url to
figure out the content-length.
Use add-to-playlist event when pasting links
Look for subtitles next to local file
